            . I am a <rs id="t18200918-234-viclabel1350" type="occupation">cabinet-maker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200918-234-victim2239 t18200918-234-viclabel1350"></join>, and live in Old Nicholl-street, Bethnal-green. On the 1st of August, about half-past one in the morning, I was in <placeName id="t18200918-234-crimeloc1351">Shoreditch</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18200918-234-crimeloc1351" type="placeName" value="Shoreditch"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18200918-234-crimeloc1351" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200918-234-off1348 t18200918-234-crimeloc1351"></join>. I was very tired, and fell asleep on a step. I was quite sober, I was awoke by feeling somebody at my neck, jumped up, and saw the prisoner in the act of putting my neck-handkerchief into her bosom. I seized her, and took it from her. I found my coat-pockets turned out, she cried out Murder! and I was surrounded by about a dozen men, who struck me, and told me to let her go. I held her till the watchman took her. They then made off.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-234-person2241">
                  WILLIAM 
                  HUGHES
               <interp inst="t18200918-234-person2241" type="surname" value="HUGHES"></interp>
